Heat the oil in a frying pan. Add the shallots and cook over a medium heat for 3–4 minutes, or until softened.Add the paprika and garlic and cook for 2 minutes. Add the butternut squash, lentils and stock, bring to a simmer and cook for 20 minutes, or until the squash and lentils are tender and almost all the liquid has been absorbed. Season.Add the tahini, yoghurt and coriander and mash to an even, fairly smooth texture.Place in the fridge for 1 hour, dust with paprika and sprinkle with coriander sprigs. Serve with the vegetable crudités.